### These sample requests work directly in IntelliJ IDEA's HTTP client,
### or you can copy the curl-equivalent into Postman/terminal.

### 1. Add a new employee
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Anjali",
  "lastName": "Rao",
  "email": "anjali.rao@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "9876543210",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "designation": "Backend Developer",
  "salary": 65000,
  "dateOfJoining": "2024-03-15"
}

### 2. Get all employees
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees

### 3. Get a single employee by id
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees/1

### 4. Search employees by name (matches first or last name, partial + case-insensitive)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees/search?name=anj

### 5. Update an employee
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Anjali",
  "lastName": "Rao",
  "email": "anjali.rao@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "9876543210",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "designation": "Senior Backend Developer",
  "salary": 80000,
  "dateOfJoining": "2024-03-15"
}

### 6. Delete an employee
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/employees/1
